    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{-\frac{12r}{r^{2}+10r+16}-\frac{2r}{r+8}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{2r}{r+2}, r\ne -8</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {-\frac{12r}{r^{2}+10r+16}-\frac{2r}{r+8}} 
      \amp = {-\frac{12r}{\left(r+8\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+2\right)}-\frac{2r}{r+8}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{12r}{\left(r+8\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+2\right)}-\frac{2r}{r+8}} \cdot \frac{(r+2)}{(r+2)} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{12r}{\left(r+8\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+2\right)}-\frac{2r\mathopen{}\left(r+2\right)}{\left(r+8\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+2\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{-12r-2r\mathopen{}\left(r+2\right)}{\left(r+8\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+2\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{-12r-2r^{2}-4r}{\left(r+8\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+2\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{-2r^{2}-16r}{\left(r+8\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+2\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-2r\mathopen{}\left(r+8\right)}}{{\left(r+8\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+2\right)}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{2r}{r+2}, r\ne -8}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>r+8</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>r \ne {-8}</m>.</p>
</solution>
